headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored a season-high 40 points, Jarrett Allen had 18 points and 15 rebounds, and the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Toronto Raptors 132-126 on Thursday night to extend their win streak to 12.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores season-high 40 points, Cavaliers beat Raptors 132-126 for 12th straight win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 19 points, helping the Golden State Warriors hold on for a 107-104 win over the Detroit Pistons on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield scores 19, helps Warriors bounce back from lopsided losses with 107-104 win over Pistons

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 23 points and 10 rebounds, Anthony Edwards added 21 points and seven assists and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Orlando Magic 104-89 on Thursday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Magic 104-89 for 3rd straight victory

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Jaden Hardy scored a season-high 25 points off the bench, P.J. Washington had 23 points and 14 rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks used a late 16-0 run to beat the Portland Trail Blazers 117-111 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hardy scores 25 and Mavericks use late 16-0 run to rally past Trail Blazers 117-111

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 32 points and 14 rebounds, and the Houston Rockets held on to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 119-115 on Thursday night in a showdown between two of the top teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun has 32 points and 14 rebounds as the Rockets beat the Grizzlies 119-115 in Morant's return

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 25 points, Kevin Durant added 23 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Atlanta Hawks 123-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley Beal leads with 25 points off the bench, Suns pull away late to beat the Hawks 123-115

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 23 points and Jaime Jaquez had 20, including five in the final 1:03, to lead the Miami Heat to a 97-92 victory over the Utah Jazz on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro's 23 points and Jaquez's clutch plays lift Heat over Jazz, 97-92

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at Los Angeles Lakers
